column6: Orange Line, Red Line; Downtown Crossing
column18: Downtown Crossing: The Franklin St entrance will be closed on Monday, August 10, and will remain closed until Summer 2016, to accommodate ongoing construction for the Millennium Tower Project.
column24: Customers desiring to enter and exit at Downtown Crossing should instead utilize entrances and exits on Summer, Chauncy, and Arch Streets. Customers desiring elevator access should note that Elevator 891 will be closed during this construction. If exiting, travel down the concourse to use the elevator through the glass doors and to the left of the CharlieCard Store. This elevator will take you to the lobby of 101 Arch Street. If boarding, travel to 101 Arch Street. Take the elevator in the back left corner of the lobby to the concourse. Take a right to find the Oak Grove-bound platform ahead. Affected routes:Orange LineRed Line (Ashmont branch)Red Line (Braintree branch)

column18: Green Line and Orange Line Notice: Beginning Saturday, January 2, 2016, North Station's north entrance/exit will be permanently closed.
column24: Due to construction of the Boston Garden Development, the Orange and Green Line's north entrance/exit at North Station will be closed permanently starting Saturday, January 2, 2016. A new underground passageway will be constructed and will provide customers with a direct connection between the Green Line, Orange Line, and Commuter Rail. To exit and enter North Station, please use the entrance/exit across Causeway Street.  During this time, North Station Elevator 941 will be closed. If exiting, return to the fare lobby to use North Station Elevator 912 (lobby to Causeway Street). If boarding, cross Causeway Street to use North Station Elevator 912 (lobby to street).

column24: If your CharlieCard has expired or is set to expire soon, please pick up a replacement card at the CharlieCard Store at Downtown Crossing or at the following select stations during the following times: - Alewife - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Arlington - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Ashmont - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Back Bay - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Dudley Square - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Forest Hills - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Harvard Square - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Kenmore - Monday-Saturday, 7 am - 7 pm; Sunday, 10:30 am - 7 pm- Maverick - Monday-Friday, 7am - 7 pm; Saturday, 7 am - 2 pm and 4:30 pm - 7 pm; Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- North Station - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Oak Grove - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Park Street - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Quincy Center - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Ruggles - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- South Station - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Wonderland - Monday-Friday, 7 am - 1:30 pm Your monthly pass and/or stored value will be transferred to a new card.  Can't get to the CharlieCard Store? Mail your expired card to:MBTA Revenue Department10 Park Plaza, Room 4730 Boston, MA 02116 If you choose to mail in your card, please include your name and a return address. Any preexisting stored value or monthly pass will be transferred to your new card.

column24: Due to crews performing necessary work as part of Government Center Project, Bowdoin Station will be closed from start to end of service beginning Saturday, January 30, 2016, through Sunday, January 31, 2016.During this time, Blue Line service will terminate/originate at State Street Station. For westbound service, please exit at State Street and travel at the street-level to Bowdoin. For eastbound service, please travel at the street-level to State Street in order to board the Blue Line. Bowdoin will re-open at the start of service the following Monday.  Customers can also utilize the Government Center shuttle bus for service between State Street, Government Center, Bowdoin, and Haymarket Stations. Customers are encouraged to allow additional travel during this service change.Affected routes:Blue Line

column18: Green Line suspended in both directions between Park and Haymarket Jan 11, 12, and 14 at approximately 8:45 pm and Jan 13 at approximately 10:30 pm through the end of service. Trains will not operate between Park and Haymarket
column24: Due to work being performed by the Government Center Project, Green Line service will be suspended between Park and Haymarket in both directions on the following dates:- Monday, January 11, 2016, at approximately 8:45 p.m. to the end of service.- Tuesday, January 12, 2016, at approximately 8:45 p.m. to the end of service. - Wednesday, January 13, 2016, at approximately 10:30 p.m. after the conclusion of the Boston Celtics game. - Thursday, January 14, 2016, at approximately 8:45 p.m. to the end of service.Eastbound trains will terminate at Park and westbound trains will terminate at Haymarket. For customers desiring westbound Green Line service beyond Haymarket, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at North Station or Haymarket. Exit at DTX and use the Winter St Concourse to Park for access to the Green Line.For customers desiring eastbound Green Line service beyond Park, use the Winter St Concourse at Park St to DTX and board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. Eastbound Green Line customers desiring elevator access should exit the Green Line at Park using the right-side doors. Upon exiting, turn left, proceed straight, and travel down the slight ramp, through the small corridor to Elevator 808 located on the left, beyond the stairs. Take Elevator 808 to the Red Line center platform. Board the Red Line train (left side of center platform) one stop to DTX. Upon exiting the Red Line at DTX, take Elevator 870 located toward the front of the train up to the concourse. Upon exiting the elevator, proceed approx 10 ft into the open corridor and turn left toward the fare gates. Exit the fare gates and proceed straight to the Orange Line Oak Grove-bound platform. Please seek a station personnel for assistance. Alternatively, press the callbox button. Board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. For Blue Line passengers transferring to eastbound Green Line service, transfer to Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service at State. Exit the Orange Line at Haymarket or North Station for eastbound Green Line service. For Blue Line passengers transferring to westbound Green Line service, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at State. Exit the Orange Line at DTX and utilize the Winter St Concourse to Park St for westbound Green Line connections. Alternatively, upon exiting the Orange Line at DTX, transfer to Alewife-bound Red Line service to Park to make westbound Green Line connections.Affected stops:Haymarket Park St.

column18: Green Line suspended in both directions between Park and Haymarket Jan 12, 14, and 18 at approximately 8:45 pm and Jan 13 at approximately 10:30 pm through the end of service. Trains will not operate between Park and Haymarket
column24: Due to work being performed by the Government Center Project, Green Line service will be suspended between Park and Haymarket in both directions on the following dates:- Tuesday, January 12, 2016, at approximately 8:45 p.m. to the end of service. - Wednesday, January 13, 2016, at approximately 10:30 p.m. after the conclusion of the Boston Celtics game. - Thursday, January 14, 2016, at approximately 8:45 p.m. to the end of service.- Monday, January 18, 2016, at approximately 8:45 p.m. to the end of service.Eastbound trains will terminate at Park and westbound trains will terminate at Haymarket. For customers desiring westbound Green Line service beyond Haymarket, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at North Station or Haymarket. Exit at Downtown Crossing and use the Winter St Concourse to Park for access to the Green Line.For customers desiring eastbound Green Line service beyond Park, use the Winter St Concourse at Park St to Downtown Crossing and board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. Eastbound Green Line customers desiring elevator access should exit the Green Line at Park using the right-side doors. Upon exiting, turn left, proceed straight, and travel down the slight ramp, through the small corridor to Elevator 808 located on the left, beyond the stairs. Take Elevator 808 to the Red Line center platform. Board the Red Line train (left side of center platform) one stop to Downtown Crossing. Upon exiting the Red Line at Downtown Crossing, take Elevator 870 located toward the front of the train up to the concourse. Upon exiting the elevator, proceed approx 10 ft into the open corridor and turn left toward the fare gates. Exit the fare gates and proceed straight to the Orange Line Oak Grove-bound platform. Please seek a station personnel for assistance. Alternatively, press the call box button. Board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. For Blue Line passengers transferring to eastbound Green Line service, transfer to Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service at State. Exit the Orange Line at Haymarket or North Station for eastbound Green Line service. For Blue Line passengers transferring to westbound Green Line service, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at State. Exit the Orange Line at Downtown Crossing and utilize the Winter St Concourse to Park St for westbound Green Line connections. Alternatively, upon exiting the Orange Line at Downtown Crossing, transfer to Alewife-bound Red Line service to Park to make westbound Green Line connections.Affected stops:Haymarket Park St

column18: Green Line suspended in both directions between Park Street and Haymarket on Feb 13-14 and Feb 20-21 from start to end of service. Trains will not operate between Park Street and Haymarket.
column24: Due to necessary work being performed by the Government Center Project, Green Line service will be suspended between Park St. and Haymarket in both directions from start to end of service during the following weekends:- Saturday, February 13, 2016, through Sunday, February 14, 2016.- Saturday, February 20, 2016, through Sunday, February 21, 2016.Inbound (eastbound) trains will terminate at Park St. and outbound (westbound) trains will terminate at Haymarket. For customers desiring westbound Green Line service beyond Haymarket, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at either North Station or Haymarket. Exit at Downtown Crossing and use the Winter Street Concourse to Park St. for access to the Green Line.For customers desiring eastbound Green Line service beyond Park St., use the Winter Street Concourse at Park St. to Downtown Crossing and board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. Eastbound Green Line customers desiring elevator access should exit the Green Line at Park St. using the right-side doors. Upon exiting, turn left, proceed straight ahead, and travel down the slight ramp, through the small corridor to Elevator #808 located on the left, beyond the stairs. Take Elevator #808 down to the Red Line center platform. Board the Red Line Ashmont-/Braintree-bound train (left side of center platform) one stop to Downtown Crossing. Upon exiting the Red Line at Downtown Crossing, take Elevator #870 located toward the front of the train up to the concourse. Upon exiting the elevator, proceed approx. 10 feet into the open corridor and turn left toward the fare gates. Exit the fare gates and proceed straight to the Orange Line Oak Grove-bound platform. Please seek a Customer Service Agent or other staff member for assistance. Alternatively, press the callbox button. Board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. For Blue Line passengers transferring to eastbound (Lechmere-bound) Green Line service, transfer to Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service at State. Exit the Orange Line at Haymarket or North Station for Lechmere-bound Green Line service. For Blue Line passengers transferring to westbound Green Line service, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at State. Exit the Orange Line at Downtown Crossing and utilize the Winter Street Concourse to Park Street for westbound Green Line connections. Alternatively, upon exiting the Orange Line at Downtown Crossing, transfer to Alewife-bound Red Line service to Park Street to make westbound Green Line connections.Affected stops:Haymarket Park St.

column24: Due to the Government Center Project, Green Line service will be suspended between Park and Haymarket in both directions beginning at approximately 10:00 p.m. through the end of service on the following days:- Monday, February 22, 2016 (after the conclusion of the Bruins game, approx 11 p.m.-12 a.m.).- Tuesday, February 23, 2016 (after the conclusion of the Carrie Underwood Concert, approx 10 p.m.)- Wednesday, February 24, 2016 (after the conclusion of the Celtics game, approx 11 p.m.).- Thursday, February 25, 2016 (after the conclusion of the Celtics game, approx 10 p.m.).Inbound (eastbound) trains will terminate at Park and outbound (westbound) trains will terminate at Haymarket. For customers desiring westbound Green Line service beyond Haymarket, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at either North Station or Haymarket. Upon exiting, turn left, proceed straight ahead, and travel down the slight ramp, through the small corridor to Elevator 808 located on the left, beyond the stairs. Upon exiting the Red Line at Downtown Crossing, take Elevator 870 located toward the front of the train up to the concourse. Upon exiting the elevator, proceed approx 10 feet into the open corridor and turn left toward the fare gates. Exit the fare gates and proceed straight to the Orange Line Oak Grove-bound platform. Please seek a Customer Service Agent or other staff member for assistance. Alternatively, press the callbox button. Board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. For Blue Line passengers transferring to eastbound (Lechmere-bound) Green Line service, transfer to Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service at State. Bowdoin will be closed beginning at approximately 8:45 p.m. through the end of service on Feb 28-Mar 2. Please board and exit the Blue Line at State Street during the closure.
column24: Due to crews performing necessary work as part of Government Center Project, Bowdoin Station will be closed beginning at approximately 8:45 p.m. through the end of service on the following days:- Sunday, February 28, 2016.- Monday, February 29, 2016.- Tuesday, March 1, 2016.- Wednesday, March  2, 2016.During this time, Blue Line service will terminate/originate at State Street Station. For westbound service, please exit at State Street and travel at the street-level to Bowdoin. For eastbound service, please travel at the street-level to State Street in order to board the Blue Line. Bowdoin will re-open at the start of service the following day.  A single train will operate between State Street outbound and Maverick outbound. Customers desiring service towards State Street will need transfer at Maverick Station on the outbound platform.Customers can also utilize the Government Center shuttle bus for service between State Street, Government Center, Bowdoin, and Haymarket Stations. Customers are encouraged to allow additional travel during this service change.Affected routes:Blue Line

column18: Green Line suspended in both directions between Park Street and Haymarket on arch 5-6 from start to end of service. Trains will not operate between Park Street and Haymarket.
column24: Due to MBTA crews performing necessary track and signal work as well as the Government Center Project, Green Line service will be suspended between Park St. and Haymarket in both directions from start to end of service on Saturday, March 5, 2016, through Sunday, March 6, 2016.Inbound (eastbound) trains will terminate at Park St. and outbound (westbound) trains will terminate at Haymarket. For customers desiring westbound Green Line service beyond Haymarket, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at either North Station or Haymarket. Exit at Downtown Crossing and use the Winter Street Concourse to Park St. for access to the Green Line.For customers desiring eastbound Green Line service beyond Park St., use the Winter Street Concourse at Park St. to Downtown Crossing and board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. Eastbound Green Line customers desiring elevator access should exit the Green Line at Park St. using the right-side doors. Upon exiting, turn left, proceed straight ahead, and travel down the slight ramp, through the small corridor to Elevator #808 located on the left, beyond the stairs. Take Elevator #808 down to the Red Line center platform. Board the Red Line Ashmont-/Braintree-bound train (left side of center platform) one stop to Downtown Crossing. Upon exiting the Red Line at Downtown Crossing, take Elevator #870 located toward the front of the train up to the concourse. Upon exiting the elevator, proceed approx. 10 feet into the open corridor and turn left toward the fare gates. Exit the fare gates and proceed straight to the Orange Line Oak Grove-bound platform. Please seek a Customer Service Agent or other staff member for assistance. Alternatively, press the callbox button. Board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. For Blue Line passengers transferring to eastbound (Lechmere-bound) Green Line service, transfer to Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service at State. Exit the Orange Line at Haymarket or North Station for Lechmere-bound Green Line service. For Blue Line passengers transferring to westbound Green Line service, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at State. Exit the Orange Line at Downtown Crossing and utilize the Winter Street Concourse to Park Street for westbound Green Line connections. Alternatively, upon exiting the Orange Line at Downtown Crossing, transfer to Alewife-bound Red Line service to Park Street to make westbound Green Line connections.Affected stops:Haymarket Park St.

column18: Braintree Garage construction beginning Monday, February 22, 2016, through August 2016, causing diminished parking availability.
column24: Braintree Garage construction will occur in phases with one or multiple aspects of the garage affected depending on the phase.  Parking Availability: Braintree Garage reaches capacity daily at approximately 7:30 a.m. Customers are advised to proceed to Quincy Adams or North Quincy for increased chances of locating available parking spaces Monday through Friday. Pick Up/Drop Off Traffic Pattern:Customers are advised to follow construction detour signs in order to access the current passenger pick up/drop off area. Customers can access the Garage and the pick up/drop off area from Union Street on the ramp from the Route 3 rotary. Premium Parking Spaces:All premium parkers must use the Union Street entrance on the ramp from the Route 3 rotary and follow construction signs to maneuver into premium spaces. Accessibility:During this phase of construction, one accessible parking space is available near the pick up/drop off area from Union Street on the ramp from the Route 3 rotary. All other accessible parking spaces continue to be available within the Garage.Affected routes:Red Line

column24: Green Line service is currently suspended between Park Street and Haymarket in both directions due to a power problem.Inbound (eastbound) trains will terminate at Park St. and outbound (westbound) trains will terminate at Haymarket. For customers desiring westbound Green Line service beyond Haymarket, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at either North Station or Haymarket. Exit at Downtown Crossing and use the Winter Street Concourse to Park St. for access to the Green Line.For customers desiring eastbound Green Line service beyond Park St., use the Winter Street Concourse at Park St. to Downtown Crossing and board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. Eastbound Green Line customers desiring elevator access should exit the Green Line at Park St. using the right-side doors. Upon exiting, turn left, proceed straight ahead, and travel down the slight ramp, through the small corridor to Elevator #808 located on the left, beyond the stairs. Take Elevator #808 down to the Red Line center platform. Board the Red Line Ashmont-/Braintree-bound train (left side of center platform) one stop to Downtown Crossing. Upon exiting the Red Line at Downtown Crossing, take Elevator #870 located toward the front of the train up to the concourse. Upon exiting the elevator, proceed approx. 10 feet into the open corridor and turn left toward the fare gates. Exit the fare gates and proceed straight to the Orange Line Oak Grove-bound platform. Please seek a Customer Service Agent or other staff member for assistance. Alternatively, press the callbox button. Board Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service to Haymarket and North Station for access to the Green Line. For Blue Line passengers transferring to eastbound (Lechmere-bound) Green Line service, transfer to Oak Grove-bound Orange Line service at State. Exit the Orange Line at Haymarket or North Station for Lechmere-bound Green Line service. For Blue Line passengers transferring to westbound Green Line service, transfer to Forest Hills-bound Orange Line service at State. Exit the Orange Line at Downtown Crossing and utilize the Winter Street Concourse to Park Street for westbound Green Line connections. Alternatively, upon exiting the Orange Line at Downtown Crossing, transfer to Alewife-bound Red Line service to Park Street to make westbound Green Line connections.Affected stops:Haymarket Park St.

column6: Green Line C branch, Green Line D branch
column18: Shuttles between Kenmore, St. Mary's, and Fenway, replacing Green C branch Kenmore-St. Mary's and Green D branch Kenmore-Fenway beginning at approximately 9 p.m. on July 29 thru July 31
column24: Due to MBTA crews performing necessary track work, a shuttle bus will operate between Kenmore, St. Mary's (C branch), and Fenway (D branch), replacing Green Line C branch trains between Kenmore and St. Mary's in both directions as well as Green Line D branch trains between Kenmore and Fenway in both directions beginning at approximately 9 p.m. on Friday, July 29, and continuing all day Saturday, July 30, and Sunday, July 31, from start to end of service. For westbound Green Line C branch service to St. Mary's and beyond, please board shuttle buses at Kenmore, disembark at St. Mary's, and board regular Green Line C branch train service. For eastbound Green Line C branch service to Kenmore and beyond, please board shuttle buses at St. Mary's, remain on the bus at Fenway, disembark at Kenmore, and board regular Green Line trolley service.For westbound Green Line D branch service to Fenway and beyond, please board shuttle buses at Kenmore, remain on the bus at St. Mary's, disembark at Fenway on Park Drive, and board regular Green Line D branch train service. For eastbound Green Line D branch service to Kenmore and beyond, please board shuttle buses at Fenway on Park Drive, disembark at Kenmore, and board regular Green Line trolley service.Regular Green Line C branch and D branch trolley service will resume at the start of service on Monday, August 1, 2016. All shuttle bus stops are accessible for persons with disabilities. Affecting the following stops:Kenmore (C branch and D branch)St. Mary's (C branch)Fenway (D branch)

It's like having a ticket office in your pocket!

column18: Your CharlieCard could be expiring soon. Please check the exp date at any fare machine today and pick up a new card if you need one before the month's end
column24: If your CharlieCard has expired or is set to expire soon, please pick up a replacement card at the CharlieCard Store at Downtown Crossing or at the following select stations during the following times: - Alewife - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Arlington - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Ashmont - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Back Bay - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Dudley Square - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Forest Hills - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Harvard Square - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Kenmore - Monday-Saturday, 7 am - 7 pm; Sunday, 10:30 am - 7 pm- Maverick - Monday-Friday, 7am - 7 pm; Saturday, 7 am - 2 pm and 4:30 pm - 7 pm; Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- North Station - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Oak Grove - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Park Street - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Quincy Center - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Ruggles - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- South Station - Monday-Sunday, 7 am - 7 pm- Wonderland - Monday-Friday, 7 am - 1:30 pm Your monthly pass and/or stored value will be transferred to a new card.  Can't get to the CharlieCard Store? Mail your expired card to:MBTA Revenue Department10 Park Plaza, Room 4730 Boston, MA 02116 If you choose to mail in your card, please include your name and a return address. Any preexisting stored value or monthly pass will be transferred to your new card.

column18: Commuter Rail mTicket Notice: mTicket just got easier and faster!
column24: Beginning September 13, the MBTA mTicket for commuter rail and ferry is now easier, faster, and more convenient to use. Check out its latest features:- Activate your mTicket with just on tap.- Access your mTicket from any device.- Purchase multiple mTickets with one tap.If you don't have the MBTA mTicket for commuter rail and ferry yet, download the app for free and enjoy the convenience of purchasing a ticket anywhere, anytime - in seconds. It's like having a ticket office in your pocket!

column18: The MBTA mTicket for the Commuter Rail and Ferry is now easier, faster, and more convenient to use. Download or update yours today.
column24: All mTicket users must update their applications by October 14th to be able to make future purchases. Tickets purchased prior to October 14th will still be valid for 90 days from the date of purchase. For enhanced security, you will have to re-enter your credit card information; please ensure that your CVV and ZIP code are correct. Enhanced features include the following:- Activate your mTicket with just one tap.- Your mTicket now appears on your home screen. No more scrolling. One tap and you're ready to go!- Access your mTicket from any device.- No more transferring your mTickets to a new smartphone. Now, enjoy instant access to your mTicket account on all your devices!- Purchase multiple mTickets with one tap.- Make split payments with multiple payment methods.- No more purchasing mTickets one by one. Now, select as many as you want at one time and buy them with just one tap!

column18: Fall Commuter Rail schedules go into effect on Monday, November 21st.  Schedules are now available online at mbta.com.
column24: The fall schedules incorporate severe weather service information and can be viewed on mbta.com on each line's schedule page.  Paper schedules will be available at North Station, South Station, and Back Bay starting on Monday, November 14th.
